US President Barack Obama ordered the expulsion of 35 Russian suspected spies over the hacking of US political groups during the election. MOSCOW - Russian diplomats who were expelled by order of US President Barack Obama left Washington on Sunday, Russian news agencies reported, citing Russia's embassy.&quot;The plane took off, everyone has left,&quot; RIA quoted the embassy's press service as saying.Obama ordered the expulsion of 35 Russian suspected spies and imposed sanctions on two Russian intelligence agencies over the hacking of US political groups during the 2016 presidential election.Russian President Vladimir Putin decided not to expel anyone in retaliation, saying he would consider the actions of President-elect Donald Trump, who takes office on 20 January, when deciding on further steps in Russia-US relations.